 on this bug? \n","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-02-01T22:54:45.247Z","updated_at":"2015-02-01T22:54:45.247Z","actor":{"username":"atom","cleared":false,"url":"/atom","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/825/0abb184a7c4a17d1a1bf2ef242c7d5d9d5fbba50_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":324291,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::BugResolved","message":"Thanks for the patience @atom!\n\nThe resolution here took a bit longer because the \"fix\" was a change in a manual process. We intentionally used lightweight validation process when our stricter validation was not possible (primarily: for properties without published SPF/DKIM records), and this process was based largely on a subjective judgement call on the risk of a mistake. The same technique was not repeatable for most sites on the internet, which is why it failed to reproduce consistently.\n\nIt is clear that having an error-prone judgement call as part of this process was a mistake. We've updated our team's process to avoid this scenario in the future. Thanks for pointing out our mistake.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-02-04T02:05:58.080Z","updated_at":"2015-02-04T02:05:58.080Z","actor":{"username":"arice","cleared":false,"url":"/arice","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/020/83152cb2d070f3f6a63c1b61bae47257722b5ad2_original.jpeg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":true},"reporter":{"username":"atom","url":"/atom"},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":324292,"is